.TH JSH 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jsh \- Jamie's Shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jsh
is a minimal interactive shell supporting command execution, pipes, and
basic builtins. It uses GNU readline for line editing and history.
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B cd \fIdirectory\fR
Change the current working directory.
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Pipes
Single pipe operator
.B |
is supported between two commands.
.TP
.B History
Command history is maintained via GNU readline.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit via the
.B exit
builtin.
.SS Internal Execution Codes
These are returned internally and not visible to the user.
.TP
.B 2
fork failed in command execution.
.TP
.B 3
pipe initialisation failed.
.TP
.B 4, 5
fork failed in piped execution.
.TP
.B 6\(en10
Builtin command handled (help, ver, clear, history, cd).
.TP
.B 11
Pipe operator detected in input.
.TP
.B 12
Simple external command queued for execution.
.TP
.B 13
Piped external command queued for execution.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR readline (3)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
